The matrix extracted is always in world space and you can use it to extract individual transformations for calculations, or you can apply transforms directly to the matrix.  There is no way to directly reapply the matrix to the Peg.  So the matrix needs to be converted into local space and then applied to the peg's attributes.  This is done by taking the inverse matrix of the pegs parent and multiplying it with the matrix for the peg.

The following is a simple example where the matrix is taken from what ever peg is selected, it is converted to local space and then the position values are extracted and printed to the message log.  If you run this you will see that the Position values extracted, will match the position values in the peg's properties.  

var sel = selection.selectedNode(0);
var parent = node.flatSrcNode(sel, 0);
var selPivot =  scene.toOGL(node.getPivot(sel, frame.current()));

var selMatrix = node.getMatrix(sel, frame.current());
var parentMatrix = node.getMatrix(parent, frame.current());
/*
